Shon Myers had so much to live for.
He was a commercial fisherman and lobsterman who had a passion for being on the water.
“He was 6-foot 6 and had a smile that would melt your heart,” said his mother, Gayle Myers of Cape Elizabeth.
Myers and his younger brother, Jamie, then 13 and 10, went exploring at Richmond Island and were caught by the incoming tide.
“He immediately started using when he went back to the states.”Myers was a skilled lobsterman and commercial fisherman who worked on boats in Maine and elsewhere.